Relation between GDP and suicide mortality
The goal of this workflow is to analyze if there is any impact of key economic indicators such as
GDP per capita and unemployment rates on suicide mortality. The data on the number of suicides in
various countries for different years was imported onto this workflow from a .sql file. Data on GDP,
population and unemployment was extracted and enriched with the existing data from the
WorldBank API. After successfully loading the data from these sources, ETL tasks are performing
within this knime workflow and we end up with correlations between suicide mortality and GDP per
capita as well as unemployment rate. Scatter plots have also been included to add a visual element
